<br>
Now sometimes I will be seen doing just what I said I don't usualy like to do.  Like say I get an extreamaly vauleuable item.  No one in my guild needs it.. well I'm not going to let it just rot.  I'll try to sell it.  But I normaly am looking towards a goal... like say to buy 4 Tink Bags would be grand!  I'd only sell the item for *cash* not trade... its one thing I hate is selling an item for X amount and some person wants that item for half of X and an item that they have.  I don't want that item they have.. I dont' want to try to sell it .. I don't care if the item they have it worth a lot.. you keep it and sell it if you think its all that and a bag of chips.. I want all of X or I'll just leave and try to sell it a differant day.  My idea is .. if I do want to sell an item.. I only spend X amount of time trying to do it.. for excalty X amount of coin or I go my own way.<br>
<br>
Now on the issue of RPing.  I'm going to try to do it all the time.  Will I not sell to someone uses WTB item... and I just happen to have it?  Nah it won't bother me, but I'll be replying in IC and hope that he will return the favor.  I also agree that it will cut down on spam, but yes I would want RPing to prevail.  As far as all the /auction causing spam.. You can filter out the /auction channel if you don't plan on actualy /actuioning.  Thats what I do when I transverse through EC.<br>
<br>
Just my take on things.. again this isn't aimmed at anyone. <p><a target="new" href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4099>Tekara Grimmhealer</a><BR>
