 <br>
There's a reason /auction is restricted to city zones-to PREVENT this from being done.<br>
  <br>
Now,if you set yourself down in say,East Freeport outside in the newbie area...that's a good place to make a Bazaar. Or somewhere similar to it  near the elven cities. <br>
 <br>
Heck,EFP is one zone away from a Wizard's teleport(North Ro) or three by druid(South Ro)...and reachable by boat as well(for those travelers from Kaladim and the like that lack the ability to).<br>
 <br>
Let's make the cities what they were intended to be-places where people buy and sell.<br>
 <br>
Don't do it in the wilderness. Heck,East Freeport even has excellent supplies for smiths,a loom for the most complex of tailored goods,and plenty to bake and brew with! North Freeport swarms with annoying guards for the more casual shoppers. Ogres and Trolls can visit EFP easily. So can Iksar that take the boat over(two zone hop from Oasis).<br>
 <br>
The idea is good-the location is poor...other ideas than mine on where to go? :P <br>
 <br>
-Morchant<br>
